cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses learning a ConvNet classifier with class-imbalanced data, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a method to address the issue of feature deviation, which is a common problem in computer vision, and thus cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of class-imbalance on traditional machine learning, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
